  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Deseed the <strong>yellow pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>\n<p>Top, tail, then chop the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Trim the green stalks off the<strong> aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and chop into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roast-pink-beef-tomato-mediterranean-veg-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped vegetables</strong> to a baking tray with a very generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and tender – these are your <strong>roasted vegetables </strong></p>\n<p>Tip: Remove the tray halfway and give everything another good mix up!</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roast-pink-beef-tomato-mediterranean-veg-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are roasting, remove the green stalk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> from the<strong> pink beef tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Slice the<strong> pink beef tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half, horizontally</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>tomato halves</strong> to one side of a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roast-pink-beef-tomato-mediterranean-veg-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tomatoes are in the oven, peel the <strong>garlic</strong> and chop it roughly</p>\n<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roast-pink-beef-tomato-mediterranean-veg-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> basil</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>grated cheese</strong> and <strong>flaked almonds</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong></p>\n<p>Add 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and 3 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [6 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and whizz until a smooth paste has formed – this is your <strong>homemade cheddar pesto</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roast-pink-beef-tomato-mediterranean-veg-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rip the <strong>ciabatta<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into large bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Once the tomatoes have been cooking for 10 min, add the <strong>ripped ciabatta</strong> to the other side of the tray and drizzle them with <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\n<p>Return the tray to the oven for 5 min or until the croutons are beginning to crisp</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roast-pink-beef-tomato-mediterranean-veg-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p>\n<p>Wash and drain the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>seasonal salad </strong></span></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roast-pink-beef-tomato-mediterranean-veg-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the<strong> roasted vegetables</strong> between plates and toss through the <span class=\"text-highlight\">washed <strong>seasonal salad</strong></span></p>\n<p>Drizzle over the <strong>dressing</strong> and top with the <strong>roasted tomato halves</strong></p>\n<p>Dollop the <strong>homemade cheddar</strong> <strong>pesto</strong> all over</p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
